pageContext.claim: “More than 8,000 votes [in Nevada] were cast by individuals who had no address and probably didn't live there.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump offered no evidence for his claim. A Nevada judge already had denied a lawsuit filed by the Trump campaign to toss out the results of the 2020 presidential vote, emphasizing the failure to provide evidence. District Court Judge James Russell said that Trump “failed to meet their burden to provide credible and relevant evidence.” He also said that the “expert testimony provided by the contestants was of little to no value.” Russell dismissed the lawsuit with prejudice -- meaning that it cannot be brought back before the court.
